    <p class="holidayDefinition">Philippines Labor Day is celebrated annually on May 01 
        to celebrate hardworking Filipinos across the country and across the whole world. 
        It is known as the “Araw ng Manggagawa”. It was first celebrated on May 1, 1903 when 
        a hundred thousand workers were organized by the country&apos;s first labor organization, 
        “Union Obrera Democratica de Filipina (U.O.D.F.)” marched from Tondo&apos;s Plaza Moriones 
        to Malacañang, demanding fairer working conditions from the then American-led government.</p>
